# reactions_text_block.net — issue #13 regression fixture.
#
# BNG2.pl emits a `begin reactions_text ... end reactions_text` block for some
# models (when the corresponding print option is set). The block is purely
# informational: it restates the numeric `reactions` block in human-readable
# pattern form. bngsim's .net loader used to match "begin reactions" as a
# substring of "begin reactions_text" and feed the pattern lines to the numeric
# reaction parser, where std::stoi("A(b)") threw "stoi: no conversion".
#
# This fixture is the minimal reproduction: a first-order decay A -> B with a
# reactions_text block appended. It must load and integrate to A(t) = A0*exp(-k1*t).
begin parameters
   1 k1 1.0
end parameters
begin species
   1 A() 100
   2 B() 0
end species
begin reactions
   1 1 2 k1
end reactions
begin reactions_text
   1 A(b) -> B(a) k1
end reactions_text
begin groups
   1 GA 1
   2 GB 2
end groups
